    "title": "37小游戏与APP正在重新构建“多端协同”战略",
    "page_range": "37",
    "summary": "**Topics:** Mobile gaming market evolution, cross-platform synergy strategies, user acquisition & retention models, game lifecycle management, and the strategic integration of mini-games into mainstream product ecosystems.\n**Entities:** Mini-games (小游戏), Native APPs (原生APP), 《皇室战争》(Clash Royale), App Store, 点点数据 (Diandian Data).\n**Dates:** 2025 (trend initiation point for long-running APP games launching data-interoperable mini-game versions).\n**Definitions/Concepts:** “多端协同/双端协同”战略 (Multi-end/Dual-end synergy strategy); Mini-games as a “前端流量漏斗” (front-end traffic funnel for low-cost acquisition and user filtering); APPs as a “价值沉淀池” (value retention pool for complete audiovisual experiences, social systems, and long-term monetization); 数据完全互通 (complete cross-platform data interoperability).\n**Claims:** Mini-games have evolved from a supplementary channel to a high-growth \"second curve\" in the global mobile gaming industry; mini-game and APP ecosystems are strategically coupled rather than isolated; adopting a \"mini-game + APP\" synergy is no longer optional but essential for optimizing user LTV, managing product lifecycles, and building competitive barriers in a saturated market.\n**Metrics & Evidence:** Nearly half of the top-grossing mini-games simultaneously offer native APP versions. Evidence type: Independent market research and data visualization by 点点数据 (Diandian Data), supported by top-grossing list analysis and industry trend observation.\n**Figures/Tables:** References a chart/figure where games highlighted in blue boxes indicate titles that have launched native APP versions on the App Store.\n**Procedures/Strategic Logic:** Deploy mini-games for broad, low-cost user acquisition and initial screening; route qualified users to native APPs for deep engagement and..."
